                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Character Creation</span>
<br />

<br />
Velvenau is an agnostic Dark Elf Enchantress.  There was no question of her being any race other than a dark elf.  I just like the dark elves the best.  This isn't because they are better at this or that.  It is just because I like them.  I had read a number of creation guides that all said that I should not worship any god - it would prove to be a problem later.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">The Tutorial</span>
<br />

<br />
I spent most of my first 2 levels in the tutorial.  I don't really like the tutorial area much so I just got my charm and left.  (don't get me wrong here - I do think that the tutorial is a good idea - just a bit dull if you've played before)
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Nektulos Forest</span>
<br />

<br />
When I leave the tutorial I go and get some money out of the shared bank and go and buy all my first level spells along with a stack of tiny daggers.  I go back to the forest summon my pet and go to kill stuff.  My pet dies.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_confused.gif" alt="icon_confused.gif" border="0" />  Summon another and strength buff it.  My pet dies.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />  Ok, it seems that my pet isn't a Necro's pet so I'll have to start doing some work myself.  (My main is a Dark Elf Necro - Level 19 - I'm used to sitting the fights out and throwing out spells at a distance)  Once I get used to this its fairly plain sailing killing the Pyre Beetles and Decaying Skeletons and I keep doing this until I reach level 4.
<br />

<br />
...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1077662" target="_blank" class="postlink">Velvenau</a> - Level 28 Enchanter on Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
