                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">New Spells</span>
<br />

<br />
I get a few new good spells now I'm level 4 - a stun, a better debuff, an AC buff, and a few illusions.  Also the all-important tash and mez.  I go and get all these spells and then return to the forest.
<br />

<br />
The first thing that I notice is that my new pet hits much harder than the last one.  It cons yellow to me and the mobs are dieing quick.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Newby Armour</span>
<br />

<br />
With my Necro I didn't discover the newby armour quests until I was too high to get any experience for them.  I didn't want to make that same mistake so I went to find out about them.  The most difficult component of the armour seems to be the blood drenched cloaks.  They are on the Arcane guys on the east of the map.  I go to have a look at them and all the ones that I can find have pets and are red to me.  Then I find an Arcane Incantor who is a lower level than the rest.  I find one and attack her.  Her mates join in from somewhere (I can't see them from where I am) and I die.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />   
<br />

<br />
I cast one of those illusions to get my faction so that they won't kill me and I have a look around.  There are two elementalists near the incantor - one to the west and one to the east.  I come up with a plan - if I attack the incantor from maximum distance and from the north then the other two might not be able to see me.  I try this plan out but shiny bob thwarts my plans.  I attacked the incantor and she casts a spell at me and my pet runs in preventing the mob from being drawn away from the others.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_doh.gif" alt="eusa_doh.gif" border="0" />   I go to help the little guy (he is only trying to help after all) but I am beaten off by the elementalists so I run away and the pet dies.  The elementalists don't give chase though - the incantor does and she regrets her decision.   <img src="images/smiles/boxer.gif" alt="boxer.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I come up with an improved plan - attack the incantor from a distance and then summon my pet when she is on her way.  This works well and I do this every time I find myself in the area without a pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Befallen</span>
<br />

<br />
I'm at level 6 and I want to try somewhere else now so I ask on the serverwide enchanter channel and one of the suggestions is Befallen.  The only time that I have been there is when my Necro was too high a level for the upper level and so I haven't had a proper go of this zone so off I go.  Another reason for choosing to go here is that I have decided that I am not going to use the POK books for travel purposes and so I don't want to stray too far away from Nektulos only to possibly die and be back at square one.  It turns out that I'm not good enough to do Befallen yet.  All the mobs that I can see from the entrance are yellow to me.  Not wanting to waste the journey I try lulling the mobs that I can see and attack the closest one.  Another mob comes from around the corner and it cons red to me and that's the end of that.
<br />

<br />
I continue in Nektulos and try the Newby armour quests and keep popping back Befallen every now and then to have another go.  I'm getting better results in Befallen now - I don't kill anything, but I don't die.  I manage to get the knack of mezzing the additional rat but I still can't get the skelly killed before I have to run off.
<br />

<br />
This continues until level 8.
<br />

<br />
...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1077662" target="_blank" class="postlink">Velvenau</a> - Level 28 Enchanter on Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
