                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">New Pet</span>
<br />

<br />
Level 8's pet is all the way over in High Keep.  Why did they put it there?  I wander over through West Commonlands to Kithicor Woods.  It's dark.... I find out that this isn't the time to go through these woods at my level.  I die quickly.  I ask about the best way to get through Kithicor Woods and the best suggestion is to wait for the day before trying again.  Other suggestions are to cast Invis Vs Undead (not until level 16) and to go the shorter route from Rivervale.  I am still not using POK as anything other than a shopping mall at the moment so I elect to just wait until daytime.  It is very easy to get through the woods during the day and I buy all my pet spells until level 16 so that I don't have to do the journey again for a while.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Back to Befallen</span>
<br />

<br />
I spend a few levels in Befallen and the commonlands.  Befallen is getting easier now and I can clear the main room given time.  One time I zone into Befallen and main room has been cleared by a powerleveller with the help of a high level character.  (This bugs me because a zone has been made almost useless to me by someone who is too low a level for the zone and someone who is way too high a level)  I take the opportunity to get the first key and go through the locked door.  I open the door and go to the corner.  I get lots of aggro here and quickly decide that I'm over my head here and leave my pet to hold the fort whilst I run away.  I just get the door opened and through it when I die.   I few seconds more and I'd have been in trouble - I would have had to wait for the SK to respawn, kill him (whilst naked) and then get the key to get my corpse back.  Whilst waiting for him to respawn you can bet that lots of other troublesome mobs would have respawned too.  A close shave that.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Estate of the Unrest</span>
<br />

<br />
I look for somewhere else to go now as Befallen has been cleared as far as I am willing to go.  I go over to the Estate of the Unrest.  I have been in this zone with my Necro and I do like it.  The trains are a danger but it doesn't often have too many people here so they aren't a problem if you stay near the entrance.  As I've mentioned I'm not using the POK books as a way of travelling so I head over to Freeport and, using illusions and invis get the boat gnome to butcherblock mountains.  I play in this zone for a while and get a stroke of luck.  I arrive in the zone and there is a powerleveller there.  A bit later he's in a bit of trouble and he runs away a with a skeleton chasing him.  When he zone the skelly (who's red to me) is at very low hitpoints and I finish him off with a nuke.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_dance.gif" alt="eusa_dance.gif" border="0" />   Lots of free exps for me - maybe I don't hate powerlevellers after all.
<br />

<br />
I get a bit bored of this zone after a while - it is too much effort at my level and the going is too slow.  I head over to North Ro and occaisonally go back to do some Newby armour quest stuff until level 12.
<br />

<br />
...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1077662" target="_blank" class="postlink">Velvenau</a> - Level 28 Enchanter on Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
