                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold">Charming</span>
<br />

<br />
I've been looking forward to charming for a quite a while.  It sounded like a great combination of exps and danger (danger = fun for me).  I read the charming guide on this site and went to West Commonlands to have a go.  I started with a green con Puma and then had a go with blue con Young Kodiak.  This seemed to go ok so I went to North Ro and headed for my first charm break (a Dune Spider).  This didn't go well - I froze up and when I did do something I tried to kill the spider but didn't have enough mana and then died.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />   After getting some questions answered from here I have another go.  I start getting success with the Dune Spiders and the Scarab Beetles in North Ro.  One of the tactics that I have been told to employ is root the target mob then, when charm breaks, you only have one mob on you.  I get killed shortly after discovering that the Dune Spiders can't be rooted and I get a spider and a madman on my ass at once.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">A Profit Made From Illusion: Human</span>
<br />

<br />
I was still in North Ro when a player shouts that he needs some help to buy something that he can't get with his faction.  He wants to buy a keg from the fishermen and they don't like Ogres.  I try to buy the keg for him and it turns out that the guy doesn't like Dark Elves either.  That's not a problem though - 30 seconds later and I'm Human and I also cast my faction spell for good measure.  The player wants me to buy 2 kegs for about 100pp each and gives me enough for 3 saying that I can keep the change.  I try to buy 2 and I can't because they are lore.  He says that I can still keep the change.   That was the easiest 200pp that I've made.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_surprised.gif" alt="icon_surprised.gif" border="0" />  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">The Bazaar</span>
<br />

<br />
200pp is more money than I have ever seen so I head off to the bazaar to do some shopping.  I buy an earring with a mana preservation and some other items with +HP and +Mana.  I also waste 75pp on a shawl which has a required level of 45.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_redface.gif" alt="icon_redface.gif" border="0" />   To make matters worse - I searched for and bought the cheapest one in the bazaar and when I come to re-sell there are 3 or 4 more traders selling them for far less.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Travelling to Kunark</span>
<br />

<br />
I decide that I would like to go to Kurn's Tower.  I'm about the right level now and I really liked this zone when I was there with my Necro.  Also, I have the ability to bind my soul now and so I can have really short CRs.  The problem is that it's on a whole other continent and I'm still not using the POK books to travel.  I dig out that map that I got with the EQ CD and refer to EQAtlas.com to find a route.  This seems to be via The Oasis of Marr, Timorous Deep, Warsliks Woods and then The Field of Bone.  I get to Timorous Deep and I just can't figure out where to go to find the boat gnome to The Overthere.  I can't work out where I am and where I need to be.  Whilst I am trying to work this out an Elf guard spots me and starts laying into me.  There is nothing I can do about this - I am on a small man-made island and I have nowhere to go.  I try to cast gate but get interrupted too many times.  I run away and then jump into the sea.  That's got to rank as one of the most stupid things that I have ever done.  If I die here how am I going to get my gear off a corpse at the bottom of the sea!!  The Elf follows me in (I guess I was hoping that he wouldn't)  I'm very close to death now and try the gate spell again.  It works!!  I land in Neriak and immediately fall unconscious at 0% health.  I regain consciousness and fall unconscious three or four times before I'm fixed.  I crawl over to the guards and sit and heal for a while.  That was close and that was the end of my resolve to not use the POK books.  I do think that it improved my enjoyment of the areas around Neriak - I had to explore what I had rather than hop around the world whenever I got a little bored of an area - but I've had enough now.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Kurn's Tower</span>
<br />

<br />
I get to Kurn's Tower and have lots of fun charming skellys.  They seem to be perfect - the charms are easy to land and last a long time.  I stay here for quite a while - ocaisonally in small groups but usually charm soloing.
<br />

<br />
Level 16 comes quite quickly here.
<br />

<br />
...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1077662" target="_blank" class="postlink">Velvenau</a> - Level 28 Enchanter on Terris Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
